output.map_title: Map to show the number of graduates of Medicine and dentistry now working in Education who are currently living in each region five years after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
output.maptext: For first degree graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry five years after graduation, the region where the most graduates had studied was London. The region where the fewest graduates had studied was West Midlands. The region where the highest number of graduates lived 5 years after graduation was East of England and the region with the fewest graduates lived was Yorkshire and the Humber.
output.maptext2: For first degree graduates of Medicine and dentistry in the Education industry, the region with the most graduates living there five years after graduation, compared to the number having studied in the region was East of England, where the number of graduates was the same as the number of students.The region with the largest decrease is Yorkshire and the Humber where the number of graduates decreased by -100%.
